Police will provide additional details about the incident in a press conference on Wednesday morning.

nib.text:
A man was fatally shot Tuesday night in Roseville after firing gunshots at police officers, injuring one, officials said.

At around 7:30 p.m., officers responded to a call on the 2900 block of West Owasso Boulevard.

In a press briefing on Wednesday morning, Roseville Police Chief Erica Scheider said that when officers arrived, a 53-year-old man immediately began firing gunshots at them.

The man allegedly fired approximately 100 shots from various locations over the course of an hour, striking one officer in the face and also hitting several homes.

The injured officer was "dragged to safety by fellow police officers” and taken to an area hospital, where he is in stable condition and being treated for “serious injuries”, according to Scheider and [KARE 11](dragged to safety by fellow police officers).

Police eventually located the suspect in a yard with a gunshot wound to the groin.

It’s unclear if police returned fire or shot the man.

The suspect was transported to an area hospital, where he was later pronounced dead.

The Minnesota Bureau of Criminal Apprehension is leading the ongoing investigation.
